    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1572a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-23T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 23, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>381. Personal for the Ambassador. Please express orally to Lord Halifax my
                    appreciation for the advance information regarding the Palestine White Paper
                    which was furnished by the British Embassy here. Unless you perceive some
                    objection I should also like to have you mention, orally and informally, that
                    you believe he would wish to know that there is rather widespread
                    disappointment, particularly in Zionist circles here, at some of the provisions
                    of the White Paper, particularly those which envisage eventually a marked
                    reduction in Jewish immigration into Palestine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
